data.description: Realtors, bring your buyers to this newly renovated luxurious 2 bedroom, 2 bath in sought-after Cross Creek for 2%. It has a beautiful view of woods and a stream from the sunroom with its newly installed double pane windows by Anderson. The kitchen features solid walnut cabinets with soft-close drawers and doors with pull-outs topped by beautiful granite.  There is a pantry with a full-size stackable washer and dryer. A peninsula with storage on both sides separates the space from the dining room, which looks into the living room for that all-important open concept. All rooms have new smooth ceilings, new  engineered 5/8" hardwood, light fixtures as well as recessed lighting. Both baths have exquisite wrap-around tile reaching to the ceiling in wet areas. The master bath has a  frameless walk-in shower and two niches built into the wall for storage. The hall bath has deep soaker tub with a shower. The electric fireplace in the sunroom stays and other furniture is negotiable. Cross Creek is known for its on-site cafe with a par 3 golf course, 3 swimming pools, 2 clubhouses, 4 tennis courts, a work-out facility and beautiful landscaping in an upscale part of Atlanta, Ga.
data.whatILove: I love the community with all the amenities.  It is within walking distance to several restaurants besides the cafe. Access to I-75 is 5 minutes. Because of the friendships I have made here, I will always have a place.  There are several groups that get together such as "Whine Wednesdays," book clubs, card groups, poker nights, chili cook-offs, etc. Because of it being mid-level in a 6 pack, the utilities are low and yet there is only a half flight of stairs to this light-filled home.
